   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Support Ticket Volume Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes support ticket volume over time, by category, severity, channel, and customer segment. We highlight major workload drivers and operational insights.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Analyze support ticket volume trends and seasonality.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Break down workload by category, severity, and channel.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify staffing implications from volume patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Measure resolution performance across segments.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Support teams need to plan staffing and resources based on expected volume. Understanding when and why tickets spike prevents SLA breaches and improves customer satisfaction.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Understaffed support periods create backlogs that compound. Proactive volume analysis enables better scheduling and resource allocation.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **8,000 support tickets** over 12 months.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 8000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CATEGORIES = [\\\"Billing\\\", \\\"Technical\\\", \\\"Account\\\", \\\"Shipping\\\", \\\"Product Issue\\\", \\\"General Inquiry\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SEVERITIES = [\\\"Low\\\", \\\"Medium\\\", \\\"High\\\", \\\"Urgent\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CHANNELS = [\\\"Email\\\", \\\"Phone\\\", \\\"Chat\\\", \\\"Self-Service\\\", \\\"Social\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SEGMENTS = [\\\"Free\\\", \\\"Pro\\\", \\\"Enterprise\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date = rng.choice(dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    category = rng.choice(CATEGORIES, p=[0.20, 0.25, 0.15, 0.12, 0.18, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    severity = rng.choice(SEVERITIES, p=[0.30, 0.35, 0.25, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    channel = rng.choice(CHANNELS, p=[0.25, 0.25, 0.25, 0.15, 0.10])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    segment = rng.choice(SEGMENTS, p=[0.40, 0.35, 0.25])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    resolution_hours = max(0.5, rng.exponential({\\\"Low\\\":4, \\\"Medium\\\":8, \\\"High\\\":16, \\\"Urgent\\\":24}[severity]))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    resolved = 1 if rng.random() < 0.88 else 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"ticket_id\\\": f\\\"TK{i+1:06d}\\\", \\\"date\\\": date, \\\"category\\\": category,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"severity\\\": severity, \\\"channel\\\": channel, \\\"segment\\\": segment,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"resolution_hours\\\": round(resolution_hours, 1), \\\"resolved\\\": resolved,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"day_of_week\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.day_name()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, Tickets: {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Resolution rate: {df['resolved'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.groupby(\\\"month\\\")[\\\"ticket_id\\\"].count().plot(ax=axes[0,0], marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Monthly Ticket Volume\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"category\\\"].value_counts().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Tickets by Category\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"severity\\\"].value_counts().reindex(SEVERITIES).plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1,0], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Tickets by Severity\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dow_order = [\\\"Monday\\\",\\\"Tuesday\\\",\\\"Wednesday\\\",\\\"Thursday\\\",\\\"Friday\\\",\\\"Saturday\\\",\\\"Sunday\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"day_of_week\\\"].value_counts().reindex(dow_order).plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1,1], color=\\\"purple\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].set_title(\\\"Tickets by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1,1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Resolution time by severity\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"severity\\\", y=\\\"resolution_hours\\\", order=SEVERITIES, palette=\\\"OrRd\\\", ax=ax)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Resolution Time by Severity\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Hours\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylim(0, df[\\\"resolution_hours\\\"].quantile(0.95))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Channel mix by segment\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ch_seg = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"segment\\\"], df[\\\"channel\\\"], normalize=\\\"index\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ch_seg.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", stacked=True, figsize=(10, 5), colormap=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title(\\\"Channel Mix by Customer Segment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.ylabel(\\\"Proportion\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xticks(rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Technical and Billing are the top two ticket categories** — combined they represent ~45% of volume.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Ticket volume is relatively stable across months** with minor fluctuations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Weekday volume is higher than weekends,** informing staffing schedules.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Urgent tickets have significantly longer resolution times.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Enterprise customers are more likely to use phone support.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data without real-world seasonal events.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No agent-level or first-response-time data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No customer satisfaction data linked to tickets.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Staff heavier on weekdays; reduce weekend coverage.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Invest in self-service documentation for Billing and Technical categories.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Set severity-based SLAs and track compliance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Analyze repeat tickets from the same customer.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Staffing based on average volume instead of peak patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Not weighting tickets by severity or resolution time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Treating all channels as equal workload.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Not tracking first response time separately from resolution time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a daily volume forecast using simple moving averages.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Calculate tickets-per-agent (assume 10 agents) and flag overload days.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Identify the \\\"repeat offender\\\" categories — which categories generate the most re-opened tickets?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design an automated routing rule based on category and severity.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Volume analysis enables proactive staffing** rather than reactive firefighting.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Category and severity breakdowns reveal where automation and self-service can reduce load.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Day-of-week patterns should drive scheduling decisions.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
